-- Economic upturn clearly on sustainable path: Nowotny
-- 
-- Mon May 23, 2011 3:50am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/05/23/us-europe-recovery-idUSTRE74M12420110523

 

 VIENNA  (Reuters) - Europe's economic upturn has become self-sustaining, European Central Bank Governing Council member Ewald Nowotny said on Monday. 

 "I think we are now clearly on a sustainable path," he told a conference while discussing prospects for the European economy. (Reporting by Syvia Westall and  Michael Shields ; Editing by John Stonestreet)